      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GINNY'S RUN (6) broke well and quickly mustered speed to win over the 530m at Murray Bridge two runs back then prominent throughout when finishing second at this track last start. Deserves serious consideration. PAW LOUIS (4) was below best at his last couple but among the placings three back at this track where he ran quick time (34.90). Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Can find the frame this time. UTTER MADNESS (1) was safely held in tougher company last start after being shuffled back early at Mt Gambier, but prior to that won comfortably by 6 lengths at Gawler (30.43) beating Paw Eva in a Grade 4/5 on March 22. Can do much better this time. NANGAR LADY (2) can fill a top-three spot.",
